<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2010-07-09</DATELINE><TITLE>Microbiology Select</TITLE><BODY>The interactions between virus proteins and host cells are intricate and impact diverse processes. Recent papers explored in this issue's Microbiology Select reveal unexpected mechanisms by which viruses interact with host cells to facilitate infection, promote replication of their genomes, and foster horizontal gene transfer.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>